-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-- mmbn3.lua — game module for the Archipelago BizHawk connector.
--             Mega Man Battle Network 3 — Blue Version (GBA)
--
-- STATUS: location DETECTION + goal are REAL and SOURCE-DERIVED from the official
-- AP world worlds/mmbn3 (Locations.py + Rom.py) and its shipped BizHawk bridge
-- (data/lua/connector_mmbn3.lua + MMBN3Client.py, main branch). The 263-entry
-- location table below was GENERATED by parsing Locations.py (every uncommented
-- LocationData row → ap_id / flag_byte / flag_mask), not hand-copied, and the
-- check + goal math replicate the connector's game_watcher byte-for-byte. Loads
-- crash-free on any ROM and self-disables on a non-AP / untrustworthy save.
--
-- SOURCE OF TRUTH
--   world   : https://github.com/ArchipelagoMW/Archipelago/tree/main/worlds/mmbn3
--   client  : https://github.com/ArchipelagoMW/Archipelago/blob/main/MMBN3Client.py
--   bridge  : https://github.com/ArchipelagoMW/Archipelago/blob/main/data/lua/connector_mmbn3.lua
--   game id : "mmbn3"   game string : "MegaMan Battle Network 3"
--
-- MEMORY MODEL (BizHawk GBA — the EXACT bytes the connector reads)
-- ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
--   The MMBN3 connector reads GBA work RAM through the System Bus, where WRAM is
--   mapped at 0x02000000. Every "checked" flag lives in a 0x434-byte block the
--   connector slurps with memory.read_bytes_as_dict(0x02000000, 0x434). A
--   location is checked when:
--       WRAM[flag_byte] & flag_mask ~= 0          (Locations.py / MMBN3Client
--                                                   check_location_packet)
--   We address the SAME bytes via the "EWRAM" domain using EWRAM-relative
--   offsets (off = flag_byte - 0x02000000), so the table is host-portable and
--   matches the launcher's memory.read_u8(addr, "EWRAM") API exactly. Offsets
--   span 0x05F .. 0x433 — all inside that block.
--
--   CANARY GATE (connector check_all_locations / is_game_complete): WRAM byte
--   0x020001A9 ("canary") is an intentionally-unused flag. When it reads 0xFF
--   the save RAM is untrustworthy (mid-load / title demo) and the connector
--   sends NO checks. We replicate that exactly — it is the connector's own
--   in-game gate, so a title screen never reports a check.
--
-- GOAL (connector is_game_complete, line ~112)
--   WRAM 0x02000433 & 0x01  ("Alpha defeated"), gated by: canary ~= 0xFF AND
--   NOT on the title/full-screen-menu (0x020097F8 & 0x04 == 0 ⇒ on title), and
--   latched once true. Mirrors the connector, which also latches game_complete.
--   The world places the "Victory" event at the Alpha_Defeated location and its
--   completion_condition is state.has(Victory) — i.e. defeating Alpha.
--
-- ITEM DELIVERY (items_handling = 0b101: remote items + starting inventory)
-- ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
--   MMBN3 is NOT a self-granting ROM — remote items ARE delivered by the
--   connector's SendItemToGame path. That path is intricate and write-heavy:
--   per-item-TYPE RAM writes (chip count arrays at 0x02001F60 with a ROM-side
--   chip-code lookup at 0x08011510, program arrays at 0x02001A80 with a color
--   index, subchips at 0x02001A30, key items at 0x020019C0 with special HP/Reg
--   side-effects, zenny at 0x020018F4, bugfrags at 0x020018F8, progressive
--   Undernet ranks), all sequenced behind an "is itemable?" state machine
--   (not in menu / transition / dialog / battle / title) and a received-item
--   index handshake stored in WRAM at 0x020000AE. Getting any of the array
--   strides, code-index lookups, or the itemable gate wrong corrupts the
--   player's save. Per the launcher's port policy that one piece is the part
--   that must be confirmed in-emulator before it is wired, so receive_item is
--   intentionally a documented NO-OP here (never a wrong write). Checks + goal
--   are fully functional; a solo or co-op seed reports every check and the goal.
--   See the C# plugin header for the same note.
--
-- MODULE CONTRACT (called by bizhawk_ap_connector.lua)
--   M.init(ctx) / M.poll() -> {ids} / M.is_goal_complete() -> bool /
--   M.receive_item(item_id, meta)
-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

local M = {}
